<h2>Overview</h2><p>Installing raised motor mounts is a pivotal step in enhancing the performance and alignment of your Jeep Wrangler, especially after a body lift. Today, we’re diving into the Brown Dog Raised Motor Mounts installation process on a 2004 Jeep Wrangler TJ. These mounts help with driveshaft alignment and ensure the engine sits securely at the right height, especially after a suspension lift.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>This article will walk you through the complete process of removing old motor mounts and installing the new Brown Dog raised versions. From tools you'll need to tips for successful installation, we've got you covered.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol><li><strong>Preparation:</strong> Before starting, it’s essential to loosen the nuts on the transmission bracket. This ensures that when you raise the motor, it doesn't create undue pressure on the old mounts. You might want to have a scissor jack handy for additional support under the engine.</li><li><strong>Removing the Old Motor Mounts:</strong> Begin by removing any air conditioning compressor components or brackets that impede access to the motor mount bolts. This might require pulling the entire mounting bracket from the block on the driver’s side. Once clear, remove the old motor mount bolts.</li><li><strong>Installing the New Mounts:</strong> Begin by fitting the new Brown Dog raised motor mount bracket on the block. With the new mount at the right height, insert the motor mount. For the other side, repeat the process once the driver's side is securely in place.</li><li><strong>Tightening:</strong> Brown Dog mounts come with 'torque prevailing nuts' which can be tightened to a snug fit without thread lock or anti-seize. They should be tight enough that the bolts don’t rattle but not so tight that they compress the bushings excessively.</li><li><strong>Final Steps:</strong> Once all is secured, re-check clearances, especially around components like the fan shroud. Fire her up to test for vibrations and check if all parts sit correctly after being neglected for some time due to mounting changes.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><ul><li>Always double-check the bolts and brackets in tight spots before tightening.</li><li>If you have questions during the installation, don’t hesitate to contact Brown Dog Industries for guidance.</li><li>Familiarize yourself with all hardware that comes in the kit to avoid last-minute scrambles.</li><li>Post-installation, monitor for vibrations or unusual noises over the first few weeks. This can indicate if your mounts are torqued correctly or if further adjustments are needed.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>Installing raised motor mounts isn’t just about lifting the engine; it's often about improving the overall drivability of your Jeep. The Brown Dog raised mounts are dedicated to enhancing the alignment and stability of the drivetrain following modifications. Thorough preparation and following the right steps make this a manageable task for any enthusiast. With the mounts installed, you’re one step closer to elevating your off-road prowess!</p>

